# Hindsight

A Windows desktop market-replay and paper-trading tool for FX, metals, and
indices. Stack: Electron + React 19 + TypeScript (strict, ESM, NodeNext),
Vitest for tests. Node ≥ 22 (staying on v22 for now; not moving to v24).
Runtime deps so far: `dukascopy-node` (URL layout for the datafeed) and
`lzma` (pure-JS LZMA1 decompressor for `.bi5`), both added in M2 slice
4b. Next runtime add is `duckdb` in M2 slice 6.

## Source-of-truth docs (read these before making architectural changes)

- `ARCHITECTURE.md` — stack, layer boundaries, milestone roadmap.
- `DEVELOPMENT.md` — TDD workflow, slice definition, DoD checklist,
  commit-message format. Follow it literally.

## Layout

- `src/shared/` — pure, framework-free TypeScript. No I/O, no Electron,
  no React imports. This is where most logic lives today. Subdirs:
  - `src/shared/` (root) — `instruments.ts`, `pip-value.ts`,
    `sizing.ts`, `types.ts` (`Tick`, `Bar`).
  - `src/shared/bars/` — `aggregate.ts` (ticks → 1 s OHLCV).
  - `src/shared/dukascopy/` — `bi5.ts` (tick decoder), `symbolMap.ts`
    (catalog → Dukascopy identifier, branded `DukascopySymbol`).
  - `src/shared/storage/` — `paths.ts` (POSIX path helpers for the
    tick + bar layout from `ARCHITECTURE.md`).
- `src/main/` — Electron main process. Currently just
  `src/main/data/dukascopyClient.ts` (the first I/O adapter, M2 slice 4b).
- `src/renderer/` — React UI (planned M3+).
- Tests live co-located: `<module>.test.ts` next to `<module>.ts`.

## Milestone state

- **M0 — Foundations**: done. Instrument types, `positionSize` v1,
  strict TS baseline, Vitest wired.
- **M1 — Instrument catalog + category-aware sizing**: done
  (commits `c4d56da`, `c31da4b`, `f6b787a`).
  - `src/shared/pip-value.ts` — pure kernel for all three categories
    (direct / inverse / cross).
  - `src/shared/instruments.ts` — 17 instruments: FX majors, JPY pairs,
    crosses (EURJPY/GBPJPY/AUDJPY/EURGBP/EURCHF), gold (XAUUSD),
    silver (XAGUSD), indices (SPX500/NAS100/US30/GER40). Platinum and
    palladium deliberately not in catalog.
  - `src/shared/sizing.ts` — delegates pip-value to the kernel; returns
    `category` on result; `UnsupportedQuoteCurrencyError` removed.
- **M2 — Data ingest** (in progress): Dukascopy fetch → bi5 decode →
  1 s bars → DuckDB-queryable Parquet store. Pure half is done; the
  I/O half is next.
  - **Slice 1 done** (`875d214`): `src/shared/dukascopy/bi5.ts` —
    pure 20-byte big-endian tick-record decoder. Bid/ask/bidVol/askVol.
  - **Slice 2 done** (`c056920`): `src/shared/bars/aggregate.ts` —
    pure tick→1s OHLCV aggregator. Bid and ask O/H/L/C tracked
    separately; volumes per-side; sparse output (no empty-second bars).
  - **Slice 3 done** (`3a791ee`): `src/shared/storage/paths.ts` —
    pure POSIX path helpers for the tick + bar layout. Strict
    `[A-Z0-9]+` symbol pattern, 1-indexed months.
  - **Slice 4a done** (`de1bcc8`): `src/shared/dukascopy/symbolMap.ts`
    — catalog→Dukascopy mapping for all 17 instruments, with branded
    `DukascopySymbol` so the fetcher's input is compile-time-safe.
  - **Slice 4b done** (`e0f96d0`): `src/main/data/dukascopyClient.ts`
    — adapter wrapping `dukascopy-node` (URL layout) + native `fetch`
    + pure-JS `lzma`. Seam at the `DukascopyClient` interface;
    `fetchHour({ symbol, hourStartMs })` returns the LZMA-decompressed
    bi5 bytes. The adapter's own unit tests fake `fetch` and
    `lzma.decompress` (one layer below `DukascopyClient`); the real
    datafeed is exercised in `dukascopyClient.network.test.ts`,
    opt-in via `HINDSIGHT_RUN_NETWORK=1`.
  - **Integration-test category** introduced alongside slice 4b:
    `aggregate.integration.test.ts` composes
    `decodeBi5Records → ticksToSecondBars` over hand-crafted bi5 bytes
    to pin the cross-module contract. Convention documented in
    `DEVELOPMENT.md` §3 and the workflow rule.
  - **Slice 5 next**: `src/main/data/ingest.ts` — ingest orchestrator
    (takes `DukascopyClient`, walks (symbol × hour) ranges, decodes,
    aggregates, hands bars to a bar-store interface that's stubbed
    until slice 6).
  - **Slice 6**: DuckDB bar store (adds `duckdb` runtime dep).
  - **Slice 7**: end-to-end smoke test / CLI entry.
- **M3+** (replay engine, paper broker, charts, UI): not started.

`npm test` and `npm run typecheck` are both clean at HEAD.

## Key conventions (short form — full text in DEVELOPMENT.md)

- TDD: every slice is tests-first. Red → green → commit. Never commit
  without confirming `npm test` and `npm run typecheck` are clean.
- One slice per commit. Commit title: `<area>: <imperative summary>`
  where `<area>` is a directory name under `src/` (or `docs`, `chore`).
- `pipSize` in `instruments.ts` is the user-facing pip (what goes into
  stop-loss entry), not the tick-feed precision. For XAGUSD they differ
  — see the comment on that spec.
